 the post-classical Greek name <i>Loukas</i> ‘man from Lucania’. This owes its perennial popularity throughout Christian Europe to the fact that, from the 2nd century onwards, the third gospel in the New Testament has been ascribed to the Lucas or Luke mentioned at various places in Acts and in the Epistles. Little is known about him beyond the facts that he was a doctor, a Gentile, and a friend and convert of St Paul. The name was borne by the character  Luke Skywalker  in the film Star Wars (  1977 ), and rose sharply in popularity in the 1990s."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":27,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705190,"age":58,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Luke Poynings was born in September 1231, in Poynings, Sussex, England, his father, Thomas de Poynings, was 30 and his mother, Ela Aguillon, was 24. He had at least 2 sons with Hawise. He died on 8 June 1294, in Addington, Surrey, England, at the age of 62."},"et":{"September 1231–8 June 1294":"september 1231–8. juuni 1294","1231–1294":"1231–1294","1233–1299":"1233–1299","1260–1308":"1260–1308","1270–1314":"1270–1314","1202–1253":"1202–1253","1208–1251":"1208–1251","about 1260":"umbes 1260","1253":"1253","1231":"1231","1251":"1251","1294":"1294","1260":"1260","1270":"1270","Bef September 1251":"enne septembrit 1251","1290":"1290","1259":"1259","1314":"1314","1202":"1202","September 1231":"september 1231","8 June 1294":"8. juuni 1294","1299":"1299","1233":"1233","Bef 1253":"enne 12